Wash and dry produce (except green beans). Peel and dice @sweet potatoes{2} into
1⁄2-inch pieces. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Place sweet potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by
2 inches. Cover, bring to a boil, and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Drain and return sweet potatoes to pot. Add @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and
@butter{1/2%tablespoon}; mash until smooth. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While sweet potatoes cook, place @butter{2%tablespoon} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{};
microwave until softened, ~{10-15%seconds}. Stir in @honey{2%teaspoon} and a
pinch of @salt{}.

Pat @ranch steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season lightly with @salt{}
and @pepper{}, then rub all over with @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tablespoon}.

> Swap in chicken or steak for pork. Cook until chicken is cooked through, 5-7
> minutes per side, or cook steak to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

While pork cooks, pierce @frozen cut green beans{6%ounce} bag with a #fork{};
place bag on a #plate{}. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: No microwave? No problem! Steam green beans in a small pot with a splash
> of water until just tender, 5-7 minutes.

Carefully transfer green beans to a #medium bowl{} and toss with lemon zest,
@butter{1/2%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a big pinch of salt and
pepper.

Divide mashed sweet potatoes and green beans between plates. Top mashed sweet
potatoes with pork. Dollop pork with honey butter and sprinkle with
@?chili flakes{1%teaspoon} if desired. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the
side.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.